    "raw": "Add optional capability x effort metadata to WorkItem/subtodo `execution` blocks so\nmodel/effort selection for a dispatched agent is groomed data, not an ad-hoc\nper-dispatch judgment call.\n\nFields (mirrors Agent tool / Workflow agent() params exactly):\n- execution.capability: haiku | sonnet | opus | fable (which model tier)\n- execution.effort: low | medium | high | xhigh | max (reasoning effort)\n\nBoth optional; absent means inherit (current default behavior unchanged).\n\nGrooming: the frequentcommits sizing pass is the natural point to annotate a\nWorkItem/subtodo with these, since that is already where difficulty is assessed.\n\nMechanical use: work-item-read's `next` hint (and add-subtodo) should surface\nexecution.capability/execution.effort so a dispatching agent passes them straight\nthrough as Agent(model=...) or Workflow's agent(prompt, {model, effort}) --\nsame dispatch-table pattern already used for execution.primitive\n(add-subtodo vs work-item-done).\n\nNote from investigation: there is no tool for an agent to change its own\nresolved session model mid-turn (that is user-driven: /model, /fast). An agent\nCAN only set model/effort for things it spawns (Agent tool's model param,\nWorkflow agent()'s model/effort opts, or a subagent type's frontmatter model\ndefault). So this feature only ever affects spawned subagents/subtodos, never\nthe orchestrating agent itself."
  },
